<Link id="l00511" /><CodeLine lineNumber="511"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This node is the base class for sequential/in-order min/max selections.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00512" /><CodeLine lineNumber="512"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Note that their fundamental difference from SCEVMinMaxExpr&#39;s is that they</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00513" /><CodeLine lineNumber="513"><Highlight kind="comment">/// are early-returning upon reaching saturation point.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00514" /><CodeLine lineNumber="514"><Highlight kind="comment">/// I.e. given &#96;0 umin&#95;seq poison&#96;, the result will be &#96;0&#96;, while the result of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00515" /><CodeLine lineNumber="515"><Highlight kind="comment">/// &#96;0 umin poison&#96; is &#96;poison&#96;. When returning early, later expressions are not</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00516" /><CodeLine lineNumber="516"><Highlight kind="comment">/// executed, so &#96;0 umin&#95;seq (%x u/ 0)&#96; does not result in undefined behavior.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00743" /><CodeLine lineNumber="743"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This visitor recursively visits a SCEV expression and re-writes it.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00744" /><CodeLine lineNumber="744"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The result from each visit is cached, so it will return the same</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00745" /><CodeLine lineNumber="745"><Highlight kind="comment">/// SCEV for the same input.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00746" /><CodeLine lineNumber="746"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> SC&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00747" /><CodeLine lineNumber="747" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scevrewritevisitor"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scevrewritevisitor/#a402d133bc2a8069432f15be4dd517589">SCEVRewriteVisitor</a> : </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">public</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/scevvisitor">SCEVVisitor</a>&lt;SC, const SCEV &#42;&gt; &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00748" /><CodeLine lineNumber="748"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">protected</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00749" /><CodeLine lineNumber="749" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scevrewritevisitor/#a1f75cac3a0eec736a85d996723c70e64"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scalarevolution">ScalarEvolution</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scevrewritevisitor/#a1f75cac3a0eec736a85d996723c70e64">SE</a>;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00750" /><CodeLine lineNumber="750"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Memoize the result of each visit so that we only compute once for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00751" /><CodeLine lineNumber="751"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// the same input SCEV. This is to avoid redundant computations when</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00752" /><CodeLine lineNumber="752"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// a SCEV is referenced by multiple SCEVs. Without memoization, this</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00753" /><CodeLine lineNumber="753"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// visit algorithm would have exponential time complexity in the worst</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00754" /><CodeLine lineNumber="754"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// case, causing the compiler to hang on certain tests.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
